ts=2026-04-23T10:01:34.846Z type=context scope=iot_project content="Smart City Waste Monitoring System. Stack: ESP32 Arduino C++ firmware, MQTT protocol, FastAPI + InfluxDB backend, Grafana dashboards, Python mock simulator for 100s of bins across Hyderabad. Sensors: Ultrasonic (fill level), IR (person approach), LDR (street lamp), LEDs (status), Capacitive touch (cleaner reset)." tags=iot,esp32,mqtt,fastapi,influxdb,grafana,hyderabad
ts=2026-04-23T23:04:18.655Z type=context scope=iot_project content="Smart City Waste Monitoring System. Current architecture: ESP32 firmware + Mosquitto + FastAPI + InfluxDB + Grafana + React worker console + Expo worker mobile app + browser demo control panel. Transport endpoints are unauthenticated for local/demo simplicity, but UI entry points use passcode 'password'. Physical/demo bin is BIN_001 in zone 'Demo Bin'. Mobile app was changed from MQTT to HTTP polling against /bins and /bins/full because Expo Go MQTT was unreliable. InfluxDB retention is 7 days and fresh 7-day backfill was rebuilt. Dashboard filters exclude legacy bad zone tags like HYD_* and BIN_001. Simulated Hyderabad bins now fill 2.5x faster via SIM_FILL_RATE_MULTIPLIER in live simulator and backfill code." issue=Project architecture, auth model, demo bin identity, mobile polling change, retention policy, simulator multiplier tags=iot,esp32,mqtt,fastapi,influxdb,grafana,react,expo,demo-bin,retention,simulator
